ENTRY       EC 3.1.7.8                  Enzyme
NAME        tuberculosinol synthase;
            Rv3378c
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on ester bonds;
            Diphosphoric-monoester hydrolases
SYSNAME     tuberculosinyl diphosphate diphosphohydrolase (tuberculosinol forming)
REACTION    tuberculosinyl diphosphate + H2O = tuberculosinol + diphosphate [RN:R09828]
ALL_REAC    R09828
SUBSTRATE   tuberculosinyl diphosphate [CPD:C19836];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     tuberculosinol [CPD:C19963];
            diphosphate [CPD:C00013]
COMMENT     Only found in species of Mycobacterium that cause tuberculosis. In addition, it also gives isotuberculosinol in 1:1 mixture, cf. EC 3.1.7.9, isotuberculosinol synthase.
